                                                                <div data-widget-id="wid__text__5f4e4cee46468" class="moto-widget moto-widget-text moto-preset-default  moto-spacing-top-small moto-spacing-right-auto moto-spacing-bottom-large moto-spacing-left-auto  " data-widget="text" data-preset="default" data-spacing="sala" data-visible-on="mobile-v" data-animation="">
                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“How great are His signs, And how mighty His wonders! His kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, And His dominion is from generation to generation.”
                                                                            <b>Daniel 4:3 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“All the inhabitants of the earth are reputed as nothing; He does according to His will in the army of heaven And among the inhabitants of the earth. No one can restrain His hand Or say to Him, “What have You done?”
                                                                            <b>Daniel 4:35 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God’s sovereignty means He is supreme over all things, and there is no one above Him.  He alone is absolutely the Lord over creation.  He is working toward the finished blueprint He laid down before the foundations of the world and His eternal purposes will come to fruition.  His omnipotence, omnipresence, omniscience and immutability all intertwine with His Sovereignty.   Without the powerful, ever-presence, all knowledgeable and unchangeable characteristics He could not be sovereign.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We have had some major bumps on the road of life this year.  As we read the history of mankind there aren’t many narratives that don’t express hardships, trials, tribulations and persecution’s through the past two thousand plus years.  Jesus told us this would happen, we must pay attention to His warnings and His instruction because He has also said He has spoken these things that in Him we would have peace.  In the world there will be tribulation, but be of good cheer, I have overcome the world.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">In Acts chapter 16 Paul and Silas were falsely accused and imprisoned after they were beaten and whipped.  They were brought down to the inner prison.  Their legs were put in stocks which were torturous.  One might say, “ where is God’s sovereignty here?” We answer with a question.  Is God all powerful, ever-present, all knowing, unlimited and supreme ?  Yes He is, and Paul and Silas believed that.  In Acts chapter nine the Lord gave a vision to Ananias telling him that Jesus would show Paul he had to suffer many things for His name sake.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Paul and Silas reasoned together with the Lord and began to praise and worship the sovereign Lord and the foundation of the prison was shaken by an earthquake and the doors were opened and all chains were loosed.  The jailer and his whole household got saved.  God’s sovereign will for Paul and Silas being in prison was fulfilled.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">This says to us today that whatever may come our way, the almighty, all powerful, ever present, all knowing, unchanging and the unlimited supreme God is with us and working on our behalf as we navigate this life and all its hardships, trials and struggles, because Jesus told us we would experience these things.  He has overcome them all.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God’s sovereignty means that if there is anyone on this planet that should be walking free of fear and in peace it should be Christians.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">We praise You almighty God for all of who you are.  How blessed we are to have a Lord such as You.  May we walk in the reality of Your supreme authority over all the earth and all it contains. May we be willing to surrender our needs, desires to Your desires that Your eternal purpose will come to fruition in our lives all for Your honor and glory, in Jesus name we pray...Amen.
                                                                        </p>
